<title>SOUTH AFRICA: S.Africa grounds five African aircraft since 1995.</title>
<headline>S.Africa grounds five African aircraft since 1995.</headline>
<dateline>CAPE TOWN 1997-05-28</dateline>
<text>
<p>Civil aviation authorities have since 1995 grounded five aircraft belonging to African airlines following spot checks at South African airports, Transport Minister Mac Maharaj said on Wednesday.</p>
<p>He said in a written response to a parliamentary question that since January 1, 1995, five Boeing 707 aircraft operating from Liberia, Ghana and Zaire were inspected and found unsafe.</p>
<p>Their airworthiness certificates were cancelled.</p>
<p>Maharaj said the Civil Aviation Authority carried out spot checks on aircraft flying into South Africa, but did not have the capacity to inspect every one.</p>
<p>-- South African parliament newsroom +27 21 4032502</p>
